    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="99"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2114</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Undersecretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Castle</hi>) <hi rend="italic">of a Conversation With the
                        Counselor of the French Embassy</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Henry</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">September 28, 1931</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-30">September 30,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Henry came in to tell me that he had reported to his Government the attitude
                    of this Department with regard to Manchuria, as I explained it to him about the
                    24th. He had a telegram which he read me, stating that the French Government was
                    grateful for the communication, that it was entirely in sympathy with the
                    attitude of this Government and felt that what had been done so far was
                    thoroughly wise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W[<hi rend="smallcaps">illiam</hi>] R. C[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >astle</hi>], <hi rend="smallcaps">Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
